 {"id":"bd-xgmqc","title":"CONFORMANCE: libc signal.h sigset helpers diff matrix","description":"Differential harness shipped in commit eed4de57. 6 functions (sigemptyset/sigfillset/sigaddset/sigdelset/sigismember/strsignal). Caught + tightened comparator on the documented userspace-vs-kernel sigset_t initialization quality-of-implementation difference (glibc leaves bytes 8..128 uninitialized; FrankenLibC zeros them; both POSIX-conformant). Zero real divergences after tightening.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:30:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:30:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T05:30:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"Harness shipped in commit eed4de57; 0 real divergences after kernel-sigset comparator tightening.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","differential","signal"]}
 {"id":"bd-70c6o","title":"CONFORMANCE: libc pthread.h primitive contract diff matrix","description":"Differential harness shipped in commit c627c961. Backend-trait abstraction over fl::* and libc::*; 7 scenarios (mutex normal/errorcheck/recursive, rwlock basic, pthread_once idempotency, pthread_key lifecycle). Pthread state is layout-incompatible between impls so we compare API contract (rc sequences match) rather than shared state. Zero divergences.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc","created_at":"2026-04-24T05:45:00.000000000Z","created_by":"cod-frankenlibc","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:45:00.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T05:45:00.000000000Z","close_reason":"Harness shipped in commit c627c961; 0 divergences against glibc.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","differential","pthread"]}
